      "agent": {
        "text": "To meet your exact specifications, the correct Siemens SIRIUS part number to order is:\n\n**3RT2027-1BB40**\n\nHere is the breakdown of why this matches your requirements:\n*   **3RT2027**: Designates a SIRIUS size S0 power contactor rated for 32 A, which corresponds to switching motors up to **15 kW at 400V**.\n*   **-1**: Crucially, the \"1\" after the hyphen specifies **standard screw terminals** for both the main and auxiliary circuits. (If you see a \"-2\" in this position, such as *3RT2027-2BB40*, that is the spring-loaded terminal version you want to avoid).\n*   **BB40**: Specifies the **24V DC control coil** and includes standard 1 NO + 1 NC built-in auxiliary contacts. \n\n*(Note: If your control circuit specifically requires 2 NO + 2 NC auxiliary contacts instead of the standard 1 NO + 1 NC, you can alternatively order **3RT2027-1BB44**, which maintains the 24V DC coil and standard screw terminals).*",
